               <head>History of Durrani rulers</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary><title>Aḥvāl-i pādshāh-i Durrānī</title> by Mīrzā Ḥusayn ʿAlī Khān Hiravī
                     ibn Rajab ʿAlī </summary>
                  <msItem
                     class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85001521 http://lccn.loc.gov/n84226939 http://lccn.loc.gov/n86066487"
                     n="1" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_3769-item1">
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="person_f7308">Mīrzā
                           Ḥusayn ʿAlī Khān Hiravī ibn Rajab ʿAlī Khān</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" type="supplied" key="person_f7308">ميرزا حسين على
                           خان هروى ابن رجب على خان</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21835">Aḥvāl-i pādshāh-i
                        Durrānī</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_21835">احوال پادشاه درّانى</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>The author names himself as Ḥusayn ʻAlī in the text (f. 1v) but is
                           referred to consistently by Anderson in this and other works as Ḥasan
                           ʻAlī </p>
                        <p>History of the later Durrani rulers of Qandahar, commissioned at the
                           request of <persName role="pat">William Anderson</persName>, Commandant
                           of Artillery to Shah Shujāʻ al-Mulk at Kandahar in 1255 (1839/40) </p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian</textLang>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
               <physDesc>
                  <objectDesc form="codex">
                     <supportDesc material="chart">
                        <extent>184 ff.<dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
                              <height>223</height>
                              <width>133</width>
                           </dimensions>
                           <dimensions type="written" unit="mm"/>
                        </extent>
                     </supportDesc>
                  </objectDesc>
                  <handDesc>
                     <handNote script="Arabic" scope="major">
                        <p>Nastaʻlīq in black ink; probably the author's autograph. </p>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <p>Signed note on f. 1r by <persName>William Anderson (1803-1858)</persName>
                        dated 1841: "Husun Alee, a seller of drugs, and instructor of Persian;
                        Heratee … volunteered to write a History of Kundahar from the days of Nadir;
                        this is the result... .", with a postscript "He was a servant of Jandad Khan
                        and Hajee Feerooz of which time he gives a good account." </p>
                     <p>Attached to folio 1r is a leaf containing a critical note in Persian by an
                        unnamed person. </p>
                  </additions>
                  <bindingDesc>
                     <binding when="1841">
                        <decoNote>Contemporary brown leather binding with plain and punched circle
                           borders. </decoNote>
                     </binding>
                  </bindingDesc>
               </physDesc>
